# ── ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Knowledge layer — EXPLICIT DECISION REQUIRED
#
# The knowledge layer JSONL file is the longitudinal governance record.
# You must decide consciously whether to commit it:
#
#   COMMIT IT if:
#     - This repo IS the canonical governance record for your deployment
#     - You want evaluation history versioned alongside code
#     - Auditors or regulators need access to the file via git history
#
#   IGNORE IT if:
#     - The file is managed by an external system (database, S3, etc.)
#     - Multiple deployments write to separate files
#     - The file grows large enough that git is the wrong storage medium
#
# Default: COMMIT the knowledge layer (line below is commented out).
# Uncomment to exclude it.
#
# governance_knowledge_layer.jsonl
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

